Now I have all the information I need. Let me create the connection using the Hookdeck REST API.

From the documentation:
- API endpoint: `POST https://api.hookdeck.com/2025-07-01/connections`
- Source type WEBHOOK is the default
- Destination type MOCK_API needs to be specified
- Filter rule uses format: `{"type": "filter", "body": {"amount": {"$gt": 100}}}`

Let me construct the API call:

```bash
curl -X POST "https://api.hookdeck.com/2025-07-01/connections" \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer $HOOKDECK_API_KEY" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "name": "filtered-conn-zr-qjtxzbw",
    "source": {
      "name": "filtered-source-zr-qjtxzbw",
      "type": "WEBHOOK"
    },
    "destination": {
      "name": "filtered-dest-zr-qjtxzbw",
      "type": "MOCK_API"
    },
    "rules": [
      {
        "type": "filter",
        "body": {
          "amount": {"$gt": 100}
        }
      }
    ]
  }'
```

